  "issue_title": "[Bug] Mirror issue discovery one-issue-per-PR rule is enforced per-miner rather than per-round",
  "issue_body": "## Description\n\nPR #796 ported the issue-discovery one-issue-per-PR rule into the new mirror path but moved the deduplication set from round-scope into per-miner scope. A solving PR that closes issues authored by multiple miners now pays *each* miner a full discovery score instead of the documented \"earliest-created qualifying issue wins\" behavior \u2014 silently inflating emissions on `closes #N closes #M` PRs and enabling cheap two-account collusion.\n\n## Steps to Reproduce\n\n1. Two registered miners A and B, both eligible (\u2265 7 valid solved issues).\n2. A files issue `#50` and B files issue `#51` in the same mirror-enabled repo.\n3. A third party merges a PR with body `closes #50 closes #51`.\n4. Validator runs a scan round.\n\nBoth A and B receive the full discovery score for that single PR. Only one should.\n\nThe pytest version of step 4 (committed on the companion fix branch) fails on `origin/test @ 41673c6603`:\n\n```\nassert e_a.issue_discovery_score > e_b.issue_discovery_score > 0\nE   AssertionError: assert 88.97 > 88.97\n```\n\n## Expected Behavior\n\nOne discovery score per solving PR per round. The earliest-created qualifying issue wins (tie-break: `issue_number`, then `uid`); other miners' issues on the same PR are credibility-only. Both miners still gain credibility from the closed issue regardless of who scores.\n\n## Actual Behavior\n\nThe dedup set lives inside the per-miner scorer ([`mirror_scan.py:243` on `origin/test`](https://github.com/entrius/gittensor/blob/test/gittensor/validator/issue_discovery/mirror_scan.py#L243)):\n\n```python\ndef _score_miner_mirror_issues(...):\n    ...\n    pr_scored_keys: Set[Tuple[str, int]] = set()  # \u2190 rebuilt on every call\n```\n\n`_score_miner_mirror_issues` is called once per miner, so the set never sees more than one miner's issues. Within a single miner the rule still works; only the cross-miner case leaks.\n\nFor comparison, the pre-#796 legacy path placed the same set at function scope of `_collect_issues_from_prs` ([`scoring.py:193-194` at `41673c6603^`](https://github.com/entrius/gittensor/blob/41673c6603%5E/gittensor/validator/issue_discovery/scoring.py#L193-L194)), which iterated all miners in a single pass \u2014 round-global by construction.\n\n## Environment\n\n- OS: Ubuntu 24.04 (x86_64)\n- Python: 3.12.3\n- Commit: `origin/test @ 41673c6603` (merge commit of PR #796)\n\n## Additional Context\n\n**Why this matters:**\n\n- `closes #N closes #M` is a common GitHub pattern when maintainers fold duplicate reports into one PR. Each duplicate authored by a different miner gets paid in full.\n- Two-account collusion: register a second miner, mirror the first's issues, double the discovery pay on any third-party fix that closes both. Cost: one extra hotkey.\n- Logs don't flag the overlap \u2014 each per-miner log line looks normal.\n\nA fix branch (`fix/mirror-cross-miner-one-issue-per-pr`) with regression tests is ready and will be opened with `Closes #<this issue>` once this is filed.",
  "merged_at": "2026-05-01T21:19:56.000Z",
